Environmental activists rescued 40 crew from a sinking ship suspected of conducting illegal fishing near the island of Sao Tope .
The Nigerian-flagged Thunder was being tracked by activists from the charity Sea Shepherd , believed it was engaged in illegal fishing .
The Thunder 's captain and crew manned life rafts late on Monday after the ship was scuttled .
Sea Shepherd 's vessels Bob Barker and Sam Simon rescued the men from the ocean .